Project Documentation: Intelligent Healthcare Appointment Scheduling1. Executive SummaryThis repository implements a Decentralized Multi-Agent System (MAS) in Java via the JADE framework to optimize healthcare appointment scheduling. The system addresses chronic issues of long waiting times and poor case prioritization in real-world hospitals. By using specialized, autonomous agents, we replace static 'first-come, first-served' models with dynamic, medical-urgency-based allocation. Critical cases are intelligently identified and prioritized, while routine appointments are negotiated for conflict resolution.2. Agent Architecture & Interactions### Agent Roles (JADE Core):Patient Agent: Represents the patient interface, initiating conversations to collect symptoms and availability using REQUEST messages.Triage Agent: An autonomous decision-making agent. It analyzes symptom severity (e.g., parsing for 'chest pain') to immediately categorize cases as CRITICAL or ROUTINE, sending priority status via INFORM messages.Scheduler Agent (Negotiator): Optimizes doctor accommodation. If a CRITICAL case conflicts with a full schedule, it identifies low-priority cases and initiates interaction using the Contract Net Protocol (PROPOSE) to negotiate slot swaps with compensation offers.3. Project Deliverables & ScreenshotsTo verify the system's functionality as described in the healthcare scenario, the following evidence is provided:Multi-Agent Environment: JADE Management GUI showing system agents (ams, df, rma) and all custom agents (Patient, Triage, Scheduler) active in the same container.Communication Flow: JADE Sniffer output demonstrating the ACL communication flow and arrows moving from Patient $\rightarrow$ Triage $\rightarrow$ Scheduler.Autonomous Behavior: A console screenshot showing the Triage Agent print statement: "Triage Decision: Emergency detected! High Urgency!" and an ACL INFORM message pop-up with content: (priority CRITICAL).4. Technical ImplementationPrerequisitesJava JDK (8 or higher)JADE Framework (jade.jar library)Setup & ExecutionCompile the source files:Bashjavac -cp ".;lib/jade.jar" *.java

2.  **Launch the Main Platform and GUI:**
    ```bash
    java -cp ".;lib/jade.jar" jade.Boot -gui -port 1100
    ```
3.  **Deploy the Healthcare Agents:**
    ```bash
    java -cp ".;lib/jade.jar" jade.Boot -container -port 1100 "Triage:TriageAgent;Scheduler:SchedulerAgent;Patient1:PatientAgent"
    
5. Negotiation LogicWhen a scheduling conflict occurs, the system utilizes a Utility-Based Negotiation. The Scheduler Agent calculates the "cost" of moving a routine appointment and offers a "compensation credit" to the routine patient agent. The interaction follows this flow:PROPOSE: "Will you accept a 20% discount to move your 10:00 AM slot to 2:00 PM?"ACCEPT/REJECT: The Routine Patient Agent evaluates its own constraints before responding.